Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay medium orange-brown. Rectangular stamp with rounded left lower corner.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 134, 7? Name Damokrates. From a die close to that of Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0337.10.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1708)
